  <prompt>
    Build `RiskDetectorHandler` — an LLM-assisted `IToolHandler` implementation per
    FR-15 that performs risk identification with code-based severity scoring. Pipeline:
    input text (contract section, email thread, transaction summary) → LLM structured-output
    call → identified risks with raw severity hints → deterministic code-based severity
    score (mapping the LLM-emitted category + risk text features to a configured
    severity scale) → structured `ToolResult` with risks grouped by severity.

    Configurable via `sprk_analysistool.sprk_configuration`: `severityLevels` (e.g., Low,
    Medium, High, Critical with numeric weights); `riskCategories` (allow-list — e.g.,
    Financial, Operational, Reputational, Regulatory, Litigation); `severityRubric`
    (mapping rules from LLM output → final severity); `modelDeployment` override.

    The "code-based severity scoring" piece is the deterministic post-processing layer —
    LLM identifies the risk, code assigns the final severity using configurable weights.
    This means severity is auditable + reproducible even if the LLM call is non-deterministic.

    Handler registers via auto-discovery per task 100 — implements `IToolHandler`;
    `HandlerId = "RiskDetectorHandler"`; lives in `Services/Ai/Handlers/RiskDetectorHandler.cs`.
    Requires `sprk_analysistool` row with `sprk_handlerclass = "RiskDetectorHandler"`.

    LLM call uses structured outputs; per-tenant cache (ADR-014); rate limit (ADR-016);
    safety pipeline (NFR-13).

    Tests use mocked `IOpenAiClient`. Cover: contract test + positive (mocked LLM returns
    risks → code assigns severities per rubric) + error (LLM invalid JSON, severity rubric
    cannot map) + config-driven (different severityLevels → different scoring) + cache.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with .NET 8 + Azure OpenAI structured-outputs + risk-scoring
    domain experience. Comfortable with hybrid LLM-output + deterministic-scoring patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `RiskDetectorHandler.cs` implemented in `Services/Ai/Handlers/`; auto-discovered;
    `sprk_analysistool` row deployed; unit tests cover positive + error + config-driven
    + cache cases; severity scoring is deterministic (same LLM output → same severity);
    LLM call uses cache (ADR-014) + rate limit (ADR-016) + safety pipeline (NFR-13);
    BFF publish-size delta ≤+0.6 MB; `code-review` + `adr-check` green.
  </goal>

