    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read TASK-INDEX; confirm 107 is 🔲; dependency 104 complete.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every &lt;inputs&gt; + &lt;knowledge&gt; file.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design Handler Surface + Output Schema">
      Define `HandlerId = "RiskDetectorHandler"`; LLM output schema (list of risks with
      category + raw severity hint + supporting evidence); `ConfigSchema` with
      `severityLevels`, `riskCategories`, `severityRubric`, `modelDeployment`. Inject
      LLM client + cache + resolver.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Handler">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/RiskDetectorHandler.cs`.
      Pattern: validate input → check per-tenant cache → on miss, call LLM via structured
      outputs → map LLM-emitted raw severities to final severity via deterministic
      rubric (pure C# function) → group risks by final severity → emit `ToolResult`.
      Telemetry per ADR-015 (no input text, no risk descriptions in logs).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author Unit Tests">
      Create `RiskDetectorHandlerTests.cs` using `TypedToolHandlerTestFixture`. Mock
      `IOpenAiClient`. Cover: contract; positive (mocked LLM returns risks → code
      assigns severities per rubric); error (LLM invalid JSON, severity unable to map);
      config-driven (different severityLevels → different scoring outputs); cache
      (second identical call hits cache); deterministic property (same mocked LLM
      output → same severity assignment across 100 runs); telemetry compliance.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Seed sprk_analysistool Row">
      Create `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-risk-detector-row.json` with
      `sprk_handlerclass = "RiskDetectorHandler"`, `sprk_toolcode = "RISK-DETECT@v1"`,
      sample `sprk_configuration`, `AvailableInContexts = "Both"`. Deploy to Spaarke
      Dev. Capture evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Build + Tests + Vuln Check">
      `dotnet build` + `dotnet test --filter "RiskDetectorHandler"`. Vuln check.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify BFF Publish-Size Delta">
      `dotnet publish -c Release ...`. Report absolute + diff. Target ≤+0.6 MB.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through criteria; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
